# __ALCHEMIQ_NAME__

Scaffolded with `alchemiq init`. Layered: `domain -> repositories -> services -> use_cases -> adapters`.

## Run

```bash
uv sync
cp __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__.example __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__   # fill in credentials if needed
# alchemiq:block docker
docker compose up -d                       # infrastructure  # alchemiq:ifnot monorepo
docker compose -f ../../docker-compose.yml up -d   # workspace-root infrastructure  # alchemiq:if monorepo
# alchemiq:endblock
uv run --env-file __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__ alchemiq makemigrations -m init
uv run --env-file __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__ alchemiq migrate
uv run --env-file __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__ uvicorn __ALCHEMIQ_MODULE__.app:app --reload    # http://localhost:8000/health/ready  # alchemiq:if fastapi
uv run --env-file __ALCHEMIQ_ENV_FILE__ faststream run __ALCHEMIQ_MODULE__.broker:app   # broker consumer  # alchemiq:if faststream
```

Nothing loads the env file implicitly - the `uv run --env-file` prefix injects it
and runs each command inside the project venv (installed CLIs such as
`alchemiq` are not on your PATH otherwise).

## Test

```bash
uv run pytest
```

## Layout

- `domain/` - models (the base `Note` model shows the field surface) + value objects  # alchemiq:if postgres
- `domain/` - models (the base `Event` model shows the ClickHouse surface) + value objects  # alchemiq:if clickhouse
- `repositories/` - data access (alchemiq `Repository` per aggregate)
- `services/` - domain logic over repositories
- `use_cases/` - application orchestration; the `UnitOfWork` boundary; event publishing
- `adapters/http/` - FastAPI routers  # alchemiq:if fastapi
- `adapters/messaging/` - FastStream subscribers  # alchemiq:if faststream

Each package's `__init__.py` documents what belongs there and shows the recommended pattern.
